[{"id":"VR802592","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a circular loop of wire of radius R that carries a current I counterclockwise in a magnetic field of magnitude B that is directed toward the top of the page.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR802592.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A uniform magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> is directed toward the top of the page, as shown. A circular loop of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> carries a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> counterclockwise. Which of the following correctly shows the sum of forces that the magnetic field exerts on the loop with the correct reasoning?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR802592_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub net equals 0\"><math alttext=\"F sub net equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>net</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>, because each segment of wire has a matching segment on the opposite side with current going in the opposite direction.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub net equals I pi times R squared B\"><math alttext=\"F sub net equals I pi times R squared B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>net</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>, because the loop is in the plane of the field.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub net equals I pi times R B\"><math alttext=\"F sub net equals I pi times R B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>net</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>π</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>, because half of the circular loop contributes to the sum of the forces.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub net equals I 2 times pi R B\"><math alttext=\"F sub net equals I 2 times pi R B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>net</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>B</mi></math></span></span>, because every segment of the loop contributes the same amount of force.</p>"],"answer":0}]